WEBVTT

00:00:14.360 --> 00:00:19.160
First, the ends of the household budget
are sewn together at 1

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:20.760
point 5 cm intervals.

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:42.920
Place a pin at the centre of the hem.

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:47.240
I'll spread it out.

00:01:05.080 --> 00:01:08.720
Combining Chieri's mountain and
the family lineage's mountain.

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:15.880
Extend the hemline by 0.5
cm and secure with a pin.

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:35.000
Place a pin 4cm flat from the collar peak.

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:41.360
Loosen the family lineage
slightly within 8 centimetres.

00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:42.800
I'll pin it.

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:49.520
Then pin it flat.

00:01:57.160 --> 00:01:59.840
Through the grain of the
fabric at the collar's edge.

00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:02.280
Secure firmly with a pin.

00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:23.120
I shall instruct Mr Oriyama
of the accounting department.

00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:57.840
Leave a seam allowance at the
hem of the household budget.

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:08.560
Sew 0.5 cm above the fold line.

00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:35.520
Therefore.

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:46.120
Secure the collar side
with basting stitches.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:53.720
Fold in half with the right sides facing.

00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:01.760
Align the left and right selvedges, trim
the fabric, and proceed

00:04:01.760 --> 00:04:03.200
to mark the pattern.
